</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,386,1212]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
The 
<taxonomicName box="[207,354,386,411]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stigmurus">
<emphasis box="[207,354,386,411]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">T. stigmurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex was first designated as a group of species by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mello-Leitao" box="[1036,1283,386,412]" pageId="2" pageNumber="38" refString="Mello-Leitao, C. de. (1945) Escorpioes sul-americanos. Arquivos do Museu Nacional, 40, 7 - 468." type="journal article" year="1945">
Mello-Leitão (
<number box="[1210,1274,386,412]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1945.0">1945</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. This group, according to Mello-Leitão, comprised three species being one of them subdivided into two subspecies: 
<taxonomicName authority="Mello-Leitao, 1933" authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1933" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acutidens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Tityus acutidens</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mello-Leitao" box="[271,501,466,492]" pageId="2" pageNumber="38" refString="Mello-Leitao, C. de. (1933) Duas novas especies de Tityus do Brasil. Annaes da Academia Brasileira de Ciencias, 5 (4), 201 - 203." type="journal article" year="1933">
Mello-Leitão, 
<number box="[440,501,466,492]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1933.0">1933</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Thorell, 1877" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1877" box="[514,828,466,492]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stigmurus">
<emphasis box="[514,658,466,491]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">T. stigmurus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Thorell" box="[666,828,466,492]" pageId="2" pageNumber="38" refString="Thorell, T. (1877) Etudes scorpiologiques. Atti Soc ital. Sci. Nat." type="book" year="1877">
Thorell, 
<number box="[767,828,466,492]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1877.0">1877</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Lutz &amp; Mello, 1922" authorityName="Lutz &amp; Mello" authorityYear="1922" box="[840,1358,466,492]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="serrulatus" subSpecies="serrulatus">
<emphasis box="[840,1114,466,491]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">T. serrulatus serrulatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lutz" box="[1122,1358,466,492]" pageId="2" pageNumber="38" refString="Lutz, A. &amp; de Mello, O. (1922) Cinco novos escorpioes brasileiros dos generos Tityus e Rhopalurus. Folha Medica Anales, 3 (6), 25." type="journal article" year="1922">
Lutz &amp; Mello, 
<number box="[1299,1358,466,492]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1922.0">1922</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Mello-Leitao, 1939" authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1939" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="serrulatus" subSpecies="vellardi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">T. serrulatus vellardi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mello-Leitao" box="[375,606,506,532]" pageId="2" pageNumber="38" refString="Mello-Leitao, C. de. (1939) Revisao do genero Tityus. Physis, 17, 57 - 76." type="journal article" year="1939">
Mello-Leitão, 
<number box="[544,606,506,532]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1939.0">1939</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Lourenço (
<number box="[746,809,506,532]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1981.0">1981</number>
), after revising this group, synonymised 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="serrulatus" subSpecies="vellardi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">T. serrulatus vellardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName box="[313,464,546,571]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serrulatus">
<emphasis box="[313,464,546,571]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">T. serrulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and established the 
<taxonomicName box="[720,916,546,571]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stigmurus">
<emphasis box="[720,916,546,571]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Tityus stigmurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex, including the new species 
<taxonomicName authority="Lourenco, 1981" authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="1981" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lamottei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Tityus lamottei</emphasis>
Lourenço, 
<number box="[384,446,586,612]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1981.0">1981</number>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Lourenco" box="[458,971,586,612]" pageId="2" pageNumber="38" refString="Lourenco, W. R. &amp; Cloudsley-Thompson, J. L. (1999) Discovery of a sexual population of Tityus serrulatus, one of the morphs within the complex Tityus stigmurus (Scorpiones, Buthidae). Journal of Arachnology, 27, 154 - 158." type="journal article" year="1999">
Lourenço and Clousdley-Thompson (
<number box="[901,962,586,612]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1999.0">1999</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
informally suggested the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,299,626,651]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serrulatus">
<emphasis box="[151,299,626,651]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">T. serrulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName box="[368,511,626,651]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stigmurus">
<emphasis box="[368,511,626,651]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">T. stigmurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but only synonymised 
<taxonomicName box="[797,923,626,651]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lamottei">
<emphasis box="[797,923,626,651]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">T. lamottei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName box="[991,1134,626,651]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stigmurus">
<emphasis box="[991,1134,626,651]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">T. stigmurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and proposed a new system of classification for the complex, based on the color patterns (referred to here as morphs) inside the 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stigmurus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">T. stigmurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex based on color patterns: morph 
<emphasis box="[749,908,706,731]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">confluenciata</emphasis>
(corresponding to 
<taxonomicName box="[1129,1277,706,731]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serrulatus">
<emphasis box="[1129,1277,706,731]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">T. serrulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), morph 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">confluenciata/maculata</emphasis>
(corresponding to 
<taxonomicName box="[616,744,746,771]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lamottei">
<emphasis box="[616,744,746,771]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">T. lamottei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), morph 
<emphasis box="[858,988,746,771]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">unifasciata</emphasis>
(corresponding to 
<taxonomicName box="[1219,1365,746,771]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stigmurus">
<emphasis box="[1219,1365,746,771]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">T. stigmurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and morph 
<emphasis box="[238,359,786,811]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">trifasciata</emphasis>
(corresponding to a previously undescribed species, 
<taxonomicName box="[1005,1194,786,811]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martinpaechi">
<emphasis box="[1005,1194,786,811]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">T. martinpaechi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, latter described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lourenco" box="[151,359,826,852]" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" refString="Lourenco, W. R. (2001) The Brazilian scorpion Tityus stigmurus (Chelicerata, Buthidae) and its complex of morphos. A new model is needed. Biogeographica, 77 (1), 21 - 34." type="journal article" year="2001">
Lourenço (
<number box="[286,350,826,852]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2001.0">2001</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. This classification system is not followed here. Two new species were subsequently included in the complex, 
<taxonomicName authority="Lourenco, 2001" authorityName="Lourenco" authorityYear="2001" box="[449,827,866,892]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martinpaechi">
<emphasis box="[449,634,866,891]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">T. martinpaechi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lourenco" box="[641,827,866,892]" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" refString="Lourenco, W. R. (2001) The Brazilian scorpion Tityus stigmurus (Chelicerata, Buthidae) and its complex of morphos. A new model is needed. Biogeographica, 77 (1), 21 - 34." type="journal article" year="2001">
Lourenço, 
<number box="[768,827,866,892]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2001.0">2001</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Candido" authorityName="Candido" box="[884,1064,866,892]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aba">
<emphasis box="[884,956,866,891]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">T. aba</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Candido" box="[965,1064,866,892]" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" refString="Candido, D. M., Lucas, S. M., Souza, C. A. R., Diaz, D. &amp; Lira da Silva, R. M. (2005) Uma nova especie de Tityus C. L. Koch, 1836 (Scorpiones, Buthidae) do estado da Bahia, Brasil. Biota Neotropica. 5 (no. 1 A) http: // www. biotaneotropica. org. br / v 5 n 1 a / pt / abstract? taxonomic-review + bn 020051 a 2005 (22 / 02 / 2006)." type="journal article" year="2005">Candido</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
et al, 
<number box="[1137,1196,866,892]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2005.0">2005</number>
increasing the number of species to five (
<bibRefCitation author="Candido" box="[417,652,906,932]" pageId="2" pageNumber="37" refString="Candido, D. M., Lucas, S. M., Souza, C. A. R., Diaz, D. &amp; Lira da Silva, R. M. (2005) Uma nova especie de Tityus C. L. Koch, 1836 (Scorpiones, Buthidae) do estado da Bahia, Brasil. Biota Neotropica. 5 (no. 1 A) http: // www. biotaneotropica. org. br / v 5 n 1 a / pt / abstract? taxonomic-review + bn 020051 a 2005 (22 / 02 / 2006)." type="journal article" year="2005">
Candido et al, 
<number box="[590,652,906,932]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Souza" box="[664,871,906,932]" pageId="2" pageNumber="38" refString="Souza, C. A. R., Candido, D. M. &amp; Lourenco, W. R. (2006) Description of the male of Tityus martinpaechi Lourenco, 2001 (Scorpiones, Buthidae). Zootaxa, 1260, 27 - 35." type="journal article" year="2006">
Souza et al, 
<number box="[807,871,906,932]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,386,1212]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
In this paper, the species of the 
<taxonomicName box="[575,721,946,971]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stigmurus">
<emphasis box="[575,721,946,971]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">T. stigmurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex are revised. The males of 
<taxonomicName box="[1146,1295,946,971]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serrulatus">
<emphasis box="[1146,1295,946,971]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">T. serrulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stigmurus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">T. stigmurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are redescribed based on specimens from States of Minas Gerais and Bahia, respectively, in 
<collectingCountry box="[1305,1380,986,1012]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. The redescriptions are necessary, since the male of 
<taxonomicName authority="Lourenco &amp; Cloudsley-Thompsom (1999)" authorityName="Lourenco &amp; Cloudsley-Thompsom" authorityYear="1999" box="[706,1435,1026,1052]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serrulatus">
<emphasis box="[706,927,1026,1051]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">T. serrulatus sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lourenco" box="[936,1435,1026,1052]" pageId="2" pageNumber="38" refString="Lourenco, W. R. &amp; Cloudsley-Thompson, J. L. (1999) Discovery of a sexual population of Tityus serrulatus, one of the morphs within the complex Tityus stigmurus (Scorpiones, Buthidae). Journal of Arachnology, 27, 154 - 158." type="journal article" year="1999">
Lourenço &amp; Cloudsley-Thompsom (
<number box="[1366,1427,1026,1052]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1999.0">1999</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was discovered to be a misidentification and the sexual dimorphism of 
<taxonomicName box="[1003,1150,1066,1091]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stigmurus">
<emphasis box="[1003,1150,1066,1091]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">T. stigmurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is poorly described and illustrated. A redescription of the female of 
<taxonomicName box="[692,782,1107,1132]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kuryi">
<emphasis box="[692,782,1107,1132]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">T. kuryi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is presented, since only the 
<typeStatus box="[1138,1240,1106,1132]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">holotype</typeStatus>
is known. New records, photos and detailed illustrations for 
<taxonomicName box="[673,760,1147,1172]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kuryi">
<emphasis box="[673,760,1147,1172]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">T. kuryi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are given. New records for all species of the complex are presented.
</paragraph>
